The paper deals with the problem of unlearning in machine learning, which is a subfield of both computer security (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework involves caching intermediate outputs of the training algorithm, which is related to the optimization techniques used in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of prior knowledge to partition and order data, which is a common technique in data management (cs.DB) and data science (cs.DS).
